  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I delete a negative Google review?</h3>
  <p>You cannot delete a review yourself unless it violates Google's policies (spam, fake, offensive content). You can flag it for Google to review, but this process is slow and rarely successful. The better strategy is always to respond professionally.</p>

  <h3>Should I respond to every negative review?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Every unanswered negative review is a missed opportunity to demonstrate professionalism to future customers. Even a brief, genuine response is better than silence.</p>

  <h3>How long should my response be?</h3>
  <p>Between 50 and 150 words is ideal. Long enough to be genuine, short enough to be readable. Avoid bullet points — they look corporate and impersonal.</p>

  <h3>What if the review is fake?</h3>
  <p>Respond as if it is real. Flag it to Google for review, but do not call it fake publicly. Simply respond professionally, state your commitment to customer satisfaction, and invite the reviewer to contact you directly.</p>
